---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About">
  <header class="pg-head"><h1>About</h1></header>
  <div class="prose gap-bot">
    <p>
      Studied CS at Toronto Metropolitan University. My focus is on data analysis —
      the kind that involves cleaning messy inputs, identifying patterns, and building tools
      that surface what matters from large datasets.
    </p>
    <p>
      I've always gravitated toward the investigative side of problem-solving. How separate
      data points connect. How anomalies tell a story if you know where to look. That
      interest shapes what I choose to build — most of my current work sits at the
      intersection of data processing, visualization, and pattern recognition.
    </p>

    <h2>Currently</h2>
    <p>
      Working on two projects. <a href="/projects/">Locktrace</a> is a spatial intelligence
      dashboard — it aggregates Toronto police data, tracks vehicle and bike theft hotspots, and flags temporal anomalies.
      <a href="/projects/">Threadline</a> is an investigative analysis platform for processing
      large communication datasets, mapping entity relationships, and surfacing patterns
      that would take weeks to find manually.
    </p>
    <p>
      Beyond the projects, I spend time on data structures, algorithms, and system
      design — partly because the fundamentals matter, partly because I find the
      problem-solving satisfying on its own.
    </p>

    <h2>Background</h2>
    <p>
      Interned at RWS Group (data pipeline automation across 12 languages) and Pyypl
      (containerized environments, database optimization). Both involved working with
      production systems and real constraints, which taught me more than any course did.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Open to conversations about roles, collaborations, or interesting problems.
      Reach me at <a href="mailto:a77ranjbar@gmail.com">a77ranjbar@gmail.com</a>
      or on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/amir-ranjbar" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
      Code is on <a href="https://github.com/ax00z" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>